Sen_description
#$@text#$@
<h1>Script actions</h1>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The script model is used to execute scripting languages, such as Groovy, Lua, Jython, etc. scripting languages. </p>

<h2>1. Features</h2>

<h3>1.1. Real-time compile and run</h3>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After the script model is edited and saved, it can be compiled and run in real time. </p>

<h3>1.2. Simple and convenient</h3>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scripts are easier to write than Java code. </p>

<h3>1.3. Variables in the action context can be used directly</h3>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Script actions can usually directly use variables in the action context. </p>

<h2>2. Common script model</h2>

<h3>2.1.GroovyAction</h3>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GroovyAction is the most commonly used scripting model in XWorker. The disadvantage is that it cannot be used under Android. </p>

<h3>2.2.BeanShell</h3>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BeanShell has lower performance than Groovy, but it can be used under Android. </p>

<h2>3. Implement a new script action model&nbsp;</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Script actions are implemented through JavaAction, you can define and add new foot models by yourself. </p>
